efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(1)
space complexity: O(n)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Utilizes a deque to store recent requests. When ping is called, the new request is added to the back. The deque is then trimmed from the front to remove requests older than 3000 milliseconds. The size of the deque represents the number of recent requests.  The deque allows for efficient insertion and removal at both ends, resulting in constant time complexity for ping operations. Space complexity is linear as the deque can store up to n requests.

